should i quit my job and raid my ira to find happiness i m the sole provider for a family of four years old i hate my job and i feel like i have no hope i can t sleep at night because i m always stressing about the job sometimes it gets really bad and i actually have suicidal thoughts because i feel like i have no way out i don t like the idea of robbing my future to get a break but it s getting so bad i don t know what else to do i just want to feel happy again you really need a vacation a nice long vacation it is amazing what clarity you can have in a few short weeks sometimes these little perks in life help keep us going i would schedule one also it might give you some clarity and time to thing about what you want to do with your life what is it exactly that you don't like about your job and what might make you happy don't give up life is very hard if you aren't happy with your job then you shouldn't care if you have to take a sick day or two to go to some interviews get another job that is less stressful and talk to your doctor yes it is alot to think about but you will be surprised how relieved you feel after taking action i must say though if you are going to get a new job take the vacation between the jobs b c you might not get another one for a while at the new job i am a year old female that is in the no way out from now till retirement my family depends on my income it is very hard but luckily i get substantial vacation time so it gives me breaks and helps me regroup find a job that gives you regular vacations and all holidays off many companies do this no job is worth killing yourself over jobs are jobs there are a million other jobs out there and when you leave they will just find someone to replace you people quit their jobs everyday if you are still feeling too depressed to take action go see your doc he can help you get through this tough time Theory of conduct Social rule Friends EastEnders Avenue Q Pitaten The Apprentice 2 Bon Jovi The Catcher in th